  "texts": [
    "This information was consistently encoded in natural language, for example \"smoking_yes\".",
    "These tokens were then added to the patient records.",
    "In order to add embeddings for gender and race to the model, a token representing each of these concepts was added at the end of the patient record [e.g., (..., race_caucasian, gender_female)].",
    "Our dataset also included information on the type of insurance each patient had.",
    "This changed throughout the course of a patient's life, so natural language tokens representing this (e.g., \"insurance_private\" or \"insurance_medicaid\") were added to the patient record with the timestamp when they were updated."
  ],
